If the `!bench` summary contains no entry with a difference in instructions of at least 10^9, then the bot posts a message confirming this information, rather than silently failing.

The bot also posts a link to the workflow CI run that generated the message.

optional: if I see this correctly and this is indeed just used once below (I think the second time you use `{formatDiff thr`}` instead) then you could remove the var `threshold` and rename the current `thr : Nat` into `threshold` instead.

Thanks Jon!

My intention had bee to have a single entry point for the `Nat`-valued `threshold`, but I was modifying code that already had a single entry to the `String`-valued one, hence the awkwardness!  I revised the code following your suggestion, so now `threshold` really is the single `Nat`-valued "variable" and the `String` version is in-lined: I am happy with the change!
